org.jruyi.common

Class IntStack

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jruyi.common.IntStack
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, ICloseable

    public final class IntStack
extends Object
implements ICloseable
    An auto-growing int stack. This class also provides a simple cache mechanism.

      • get

        public static IntStack get()
        Gets an object of IntStack from the local cache of the current thread, if the cache is not empty. Otherwise a new object is created and returned.
        Returns:
        an object of IntStack.

      • get

        public static IntStack get(int capacity)
        Gets an object of IntStack from the local cache of the current thread, if the cache is not empty. Otherwise a new object is created and returned.

        The returned object is ensured to have the minimum capacity of the given capacity.

        Parameters:
        capacity - the minimum capacity of the IntStack to be returned.
        Returns:
        an object of IntStack.

      • push

        public void push(int i)

      • pop

        public int pop()
        Returns and removes the int at the top of this stack. The size of this stack is reduced by 1.
